Title: Acetatoaqua(di-2-pyridylamine)isothiocyanatocopper(II)

Abstract: In the structure of the title complex, [Cu(C2H3O2)(NCS)(C10H9N3)(H2O)], the CuII atom displays a square-pyramidal geometry, coordinated by two N atoms of the di-2-pyridyl­amine ligand, the N atom from the isothio­cyanate ligand and two O atoms from the acetate group and the water mol­ecule. The structure displays inter­molecular hydrogen bonding.
